  "source": "Corollary:\n. \"Corollary 4.8\"\nof:\n. \"Lemma 4.5 (Pigeonhole Principle)\"\nthen:\n. \\set.theoretic.naturals is? \\(infinite)::set\nDocumented:\n. description: \"The set $\\omega$ is infinite. Indeed $\\omega \\sim \\omega \\setminus \\{0\\}$ under the map $n \\mapsto n^+$, so $\\omega$ is equivalent to a proper subset of itself, which no finite set can be.\"\nId: \"f365ada7-50a7-4c7f-b4ec-3910633d25e6\"",
